# Evaluation Criteria

Evaluate against these five criteria:

1. **Does it do what it is supposed to do?** — The change request is fully applied. New features have fresh `[F00N]` IDs continuing the sequence. Modified features retain their original IDs with the `[EXISTING-F...]` prefix. Deleted features have the `[DELETED-F...]` prefix.
2. **Does it work well?** — Unchanged features are preserved exactly as they were, with the `[EXISTING-F...]` prefix. No features were accidentally dropped or duplicated.
3. **Is it reasonably well designed?** — Feature ID sequencing is correct. No gaps or duplicates in IDs.
4. **Is it safe?** — Unaffected preferences are preserved without modification. No information was lost from the original structured input beyond what the change request explicitly addresses.
5. **No obvious scaling issues?** — The output format matches the Structured Input format exactly and is parseable by downstream agents.

